  "local_port": 42400,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "PAN Card: I lost my Aadhaar card. How can I get a second copy?",
  "response": "If you\u2019ve lost your **Aadhaar card**, don\u2019t worry\u2014you can easily get a **reprint** or **download** a copy online. Here\u2019s how:\n\n---\n\n### Steps to Get a Second Copy of Your Aadhaar Card:\n\n1. **Visit the Official UIDAI Website**:\n   - Go to the UIDAI portal: [https://uidai.gov.in/](https://uidai.gov.in/)\n\n2. **Find the \"Order Aadhaar Reprint\" Option**:\n   - On the homepage, look for the \"My Aadhaar\" section and click on \"Order Aadhaar Reprint.\"\n\n3. **Enter Your Details**:\n   - You\u2019ll need your **12-digit Aadhaar number** or **16-digit Virtual ID (VID)**.\n   - If you don\u2019t remember your Aadhaar number or VID, you can retrieve it using your registered mobile number.\n\n4. **Verify via OTP**:\n   - An OTP will be sent to your registered mobile number linked with your Aadhaar. Enter the OTP to verify your identity.\n\n5. **Pay the Reprint Fee**:\n   - A nominal fee of **\u20b950** is charged for the reprint. Payment can be made via debit/credit card, net banking, or UPI.\n\n6. **Confirm and Download**:\n   - After payment, you\u2019ll receive a confirmation. You can download a **soft copy** (e-Aadhaar) immediately, or you can request a **physical copy** to be delivered to your registered address.\n\n---\n\n### Alternative: Download e-Aadhaar\nIf you only need a digital copy, you can download your **e-Aadhaar** for free:\n1. Visit **https://eaadhaar.uidai.gov.in/**\n2. Enter your details and verify via OTP.\n3. Download the e-Aadhaar PDF, which is password-protected (password is your **PIN Code**).\n\n---\n\n### Important Notes:\n- Ensure your **mobile number** is linked to your Aadhaar for OTP verification.\n- If your mobile number is not registered or has changed, visit the nearest **Aadhaar Enrollment Center** to update it.\n- The e-Aadhaar is equally valid as the physical card and can be used for all official purposes.\n\nLet me know if you need further assistance!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
